title: Mainland processing plants supplying chilled beef to Hong Kong increased to six
content_text:
p>
    A spokesman for the Food and Health Bureau (FHB) announced today (January 
    10) that the number of processing plants in the Mainland eligible to supply 
    chilled beef to Hong Kong has been increased from one to six. The additional 
    five processing plants are located in Inner Mongolia, Heilongjiang and 
    Chongqing respectively.  To ensure food safety, all chilled beef imported from the Mainland must come 
    from the processing plants registered for export of chilled beef under the 
    State General Administration of Quality Supervision, Inspection and

State General Administration of Quality Supervision, Inspection and 
    Quarantine (AQSIQ). These processing plants are recommended by the AQSIQ to 
    the Centre for Food Safety (CFS), with further on-site and audit inspections 
    conducted by CFS staff to ensure compliance with the relevant food hygiene 
    and safety requirements.  "In December 2010, the FHB reached an agreement with the AQSIQ on the 
    arrangement for the import of Mainland chilled beef into Hong Kong. Since

arrangement for the import of Mainland chilled beef into Hong Kong. Since 
    then, both sides have been in active discussion with a view to increasing 
    the number of eligible processing plants supplying chilled beef to Hong 
    Kong. The five aforesaid processing plants were recommended by the AQSIQ. 
    The CFS has completed its inspection of the processing plants and their 
    respective cattle farms to ensure compliance with the relevant food hygiene 
    and safety standards," the spokesman said. "The import of chilled beef from the Mainland is conducive to stabilising

the supply of beef in Hong Kong, thus maintaining food prices at a stable level." Detailed information about the six processing plants in the Mainland eligible for supplying chilled beef to Hong Kong is available on the CFS website (www.cfs.gov.hk/english/links/links_rs/links_rs.html). The Government strives to maintain the openness and competitiveness of the

local non-staple food market. To this end, the FHB has been actively seeking 
    to increase food sources so as to diversify food types. At present, chilled 
    pork, chilled chicken and other chilled poultry meat (including geese, duck 
    and pigeon) are imported from the Mainland into Hong Kong.  Importers who are interested in importing chilled beef from the Mainland can 
    proceed with the application for import by obtaining an application form at 
    the Food Importer/Distributor Registration and Import Licensing Office of

the Food Importer/Distributor Registration and Import Licensing Office of CFS in Room 119, 1/F, 258 Queen's Road East, Wan Chai, or by downloading the form from the CFS website www.cfs.gov.hk/english/public/public_fi/files/fehb161.pdf. Enquiries can be made on 2156 3012.
